Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 03 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
Then I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Cervix uteri mass' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected
And 'I describe' button is preselected

When I select 'I know' button
Then 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown is enabled
When I select 'Cervical carcinoma' from 'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown
And I select 'Differential diagnosis' tab
Then 'Stage I: Limited to the cervix' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage II: Extension beyond the cervix' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage III: Invasion of the lower third of the vagina or the pelvic wall or hydro-nephrosis/"silent kidney"' is enabled
And 'Stage IV: Advanced tumor stage' is enabled

When I select 'Stage I: Limited to the cervix' radio button
Then '1B: Macroinvasive lesion' checkbox is enabled

When I select '1B: Macroinvasive lesion' checkbox
Then 'Further information*' dropdown is enabled

When I click on any option in the 'Further information*' dropdown
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage II: Extension beyond the cervix' radio button
Then 'Details stage II*' drodown is enabled

When I select 'IIA: Invasion of the upper or middle third of the vagina' from the 'Details stage II*' drodown
Then 'Further information*' dropdown is enabled

When I click on any option in the 'Further information*' dropdown
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage III: Invasion of the lower third of the vagina or the pelvic wall or hydro- nephrosis/"silent kidney"' radio button
Then 'Details stage III*' dropdown is enabled

When I click on any option in the 'Details stage III*' dropdown
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage IV: Advanced tumor stage' drodown
Then 'Details stage IV*' dropdown is enabled

When I select 'Characterization I' tab
And I select 'Lymphoma' from the  'Differential diagnosis 1*' dropdown
Then the option is select


When I select 'Differential diagnosis' tab
And I select 'Cervical carcinoma' from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown
Then 'Stage I: Limited to the cervix' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage II: Extension beyond the cervix' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage III: Invasion of the lower third of the vagina or the pelvic wall or hydro-nephrosis/"silent kidney"' is enabled
And 'Stage IV: Advanced tumor stage' is enabled
And 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Stage I: Limited to the cervix' radio button
Then '1B: Macroinvasive lesion' checkbox is enabled

When I select '1B: Macroinvasive lesion' checkbox
Then 'Further information*' dropdown is enabled

When I click on any option in the 'Further information*' dropdown
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage II: Extension beyond the cervix' radio button
Then 'Details stage II*' drodown is enabled

When I select 'IIA: Invasion of the upper or middle third of the vagina' from the 'Details stage II*' drodown
Then 'Further information*' dropdown is enabled

When I click on any option in the 'Further information*' dropdown
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage III: Invasion of the lower third of the vagina or the pelvic wall or hydro- nephrosis/"silent kidney"' radio button
Then 'Details stage III*' dropdown is enabled

When I click on any option in the 'Details stage III*' dropdown
Then an option is selected

When I select 'Stage IV: Advanced tumor stage' drodown
Then 'Details stage IV*' dropdown is enabled



























